Basic Commands
ls - List directory contents
cd - Change the current directory
pwd - Print the current working directory
mkdir - Make a new directory
rmdir - Remove an empty directory
cp - Copy files and directories
mv - Move/rename files and directories
rm - Remove files and directories
touch - Create an empty file or update the timestamp of a file
cat - Concatenate and display file contents
echo - Display a line of text
man - Display the manual for a command
chmod - Change file permissions
chown - Change file owner and group
find - Search for files in a directory hierarchy
grep - Search text using patterns
head - Output the first part of files
tail - Output the last part of files
df - Display disk space usage
du - Estimate file space usage
ps - Report a snapshot of current processes
kill - Terminate processes by PID
top - Display Linux tasks (system monitoring)
nano - A simple text editor
vi/vim - A more advanced text editor
Intermediate Commands
tar - Archive files
gzip/gunzip - Compress and decompress files
zip/unzip - Package and compress (archive) files
scp - Secure copy (remote file copy program)
rsync - Remote file and directory synchronization
wget - Retrieve files from the web
curl - Transfer data from or to a server
ssh - OpenSSH SSH client (remote login program)
chmod - Change file modes or Access Control Lists
chown - Change file owner and group
df - Report file system disk space usage
du - Estimate file space usage
alias - Create an alias for a command
awk - Pattern scanning and processing language
sed - Stream editor for filtering and transforming text
xargs - Build and execute command lines from standard input
crontab - Schedule periodic background jobs
at - Schedule commands to run at a particular time
systemctl - Control the systemd system and service manager
journalctl - Query and display messages from the journal
ln - Create hard and symbolic links
netstat - Print network connections, routing tables, interface statistics, masquerade connections, and multicast memberships
iptables - Administration tool for IPv4 packet filtering and NAT
ufw - Uncomplicated Firewall, front-end for iptables
Advanced Commands
iptables - Administration tool for IPv4 packet filtering and NAT
firewalld - Dynamic firewall management tool with D-Bus interface
tcpdump - Command-line packet analyzer
nmap - Network exploration tool and security/port scanner
strace - Trace system calls and signals
lsof - List open files
iotop - Display I/O usage by processes or threads
htop - Interactive process viewer
dmesg - Print or control the kernel ring buffer
sysctl - Configure kernel parameters at runtime
systat - Collection of performance monitoring tools
vmstat - Report virtual memory statistics
sar - Collect, report, or save system activity information
ip - Show/manipulate routing, devices, policy routing, and tunnels
docker - Docker container management
kubernetes - Container orchestration tool
ansible - Automation tool for managing remote systems
chef - Configuration management tool
puppet - IT automation tool for configuration management
terraform - Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tool
git - Distributed version control system
jenkins - Automation server for CI/CD
prometheus - Monitoring and alerting toolkit
grafana - Open-source platform for monitoring and observability
elk stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana) - Log management and analytics
